# Command Reference:
# CMD 16  = WAYPOINT
# CMD 20  = RTL
# CMD 22  = TAKEOFF
# CMD 206 = DO_SET_CAM_TRIGG_DIST

# Waypoint Descriptions:
# 0: Home
# 1: Takeoff to 100m
# 2: Enable camera triggering (every 50m)
# 3-6: Survey grid waypoints
# 7: Disable camera triggering
# 8: RTL

# DO_SET_CAM_TRIGG_DIST Parameters:
# Waypoint 2:
#   Param1: 1.00 = Enable triggering
#   Param2: 50.00 = Distance between shots (meters)
#
# Waypoint 7:
#   Param1: 0.00 = Disable triggering

# Camera Configuration Parameters:
# CAM_TRIGG_TYPE,1        # Servo trigger
# CAM_DURATION,10         # 10ms pulse
# CAM_SERVO_ON,1900       # Servo PWM high
# CAM_SERVO_OFF,1100      # Servo PWM low
# CAM_TRIGG_DIST,50       # Distance trigger (meters)
# SERVO9_FUNCTION,10      # Camera trigger on servo 9

# Expected Photos:
# Grid distance: ~1200m total
# Trigger interval: 50m
# Expected photos: ~24 images

# Loading instructions:
# 1. Configure camera parameters first
# 2. Load mission in Mission Planner
# 3. Verify camera trigger on servo output
# 4. Test trigger with multimeter before flight
# 5. Ensure SD card in camera with space
